cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper deals with the security analysis of a network protocol (PTP) and proposes new security extensions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves network-based defenses, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The proposed security extensions involve the use of elliptic-curve cryptography, which falls under the category cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the implementation and evaluation of the proposed schemes, which suggests the category cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper involves the use of Public-Key signatures, which falls under the category cs.IT (Information Theory).
